      <h2 class="section-heading">
        Press Contact
      </h2>
      <p class="body-text">
        For press inquiries, interviews, and media requests:<br />
        <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:edson@edsonpavoni.com">edson@edsonpavoni.com</a><br />
        <strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://orbitaltemple.com">orbitaltemple.com</a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- About the Project -->
    <section class="press-section">
      <h2 class="section-heading">
        About the Project
      </h2>
      <p class="body-text">
        Orbital Temple is an artwork and a satellite that aims to be the first radically inclusive temple, a sacred space accessible to all, built where no walls can reach. Created by Brazilian artist Edson Pavoni, the project invites people from around the world to send the name of someone they wish to remember. These names are transmitted to a satellite in orbit, creating a collective memorial beyond borders, nations, and religions.
      </p>
      <p class="body-text body-text--section-end">
        Through a website available in 246 languages, participants engage in a breathing ritual before sending a name into space. The Orbital Temple explores themes of inclusion, memory, and our shared humanity, questioning why no physical temple on Earth can truly welcome everyone, and proposing space as the only place where radical inclusivity might exist.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Key Facts -->
    <section class="press-section">
      <h2 class="section-heading">
        Key Facts
      </h2>
      <ul class="body-text" style="list-style: none; padding-left: 0;">
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Artist:</strong> Edson Pavoni (Brazil)</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Project Type:</strong> Satellite artwork, participatory installation, web-based ritual</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Launch Date:</strong> November 28, 2025</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Launch Location:</strong> ISRO (Indian Space Research Organisation), India</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Satellite:</strong> 1P PocketQube, 50x58x64mm, 245g</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Orbit:</strong> 525km altitude, Sun-synchronous</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Languages:</strong> 246 languages supported via Google Translation API</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Participation:</strong> Free, open to everyone globally</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Ground Station:</strong> 6m diameter antenna/sculpture installation</li>
      </ul>

