    <section class="press-section">
      <h2 class="section-heading">
        Artist Statement (Excerpt)
      </h2>
      <p class="body-text" style="font-style: italic;">
        "No temple can be radically inclusive. There is no place on Earth that can hold the universal sacred. Yet all peoples who ever lived built temples, proof that something sacred unites us. Something that sees no borders. Something that deserves a place of its own."
      </p>
      <p class="body-text body-text--section-end" style="font-style: italic;">
        "Where could we build such a temple? Where no walls can reach, no nation can claim, no religion can rule. Space."
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Featured In / Press Coverage -->
    <section class="press-section">
      <h2 class="section-heading">
        Featured In / Press Coverage
      </h2>
      <p class="body-text">
        <em>Press coverage and features will be added as they become available. For the latest updates, please contact our press team.</em>
      </p>
      <p class="body-text body-text--section-end">
        Previous exhibitions and features include presentations at the 13th Mercosul Bienal, recognition from the Lumen Prize, and selection by the Brazilian Institute of Space Research (INPE).
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Technical Specifications -->
    <section class="press-section">
      <h2 class="section-heading">
        Technical Specifications
      </h2>

      <h3 class="subsection-heading">Satellite</h3>
      <ul class="body-text" style="list-style: none; padding-left: 0;">
        <li>Dimensions: 50 x 58 x 64 mm</li>
        <li>Classification: 1P PocketQube</li>
        <li>Weight: 245g</li>
        <li>Materials: Aluminum, gold, fiberglass, electronic components</li>
        <li>Orbit: Altitude 525 ± 25 km; Inclination: SSO 97.6 ± 0.1°</li>
        <li>Launch: November 28, 2025 via ISRO, India</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="subsection-heading">Antenna/Sculpture</h3>
      <ul class="body-text" style="list-style: none; padding-left: 0;">
        <li>Dimensions: 6m diameter x 1.2m height</li>
        <li>Weight: 46 kg</li>
        <li>Materials: Aluminum, epoxy mirrored board, golden aluminum dome suspended through scaffolding structure</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="subsection-heading">Radio Specifications</h3>
      <p class="body-text body-text--section-end">
        Downlink: 437 MHz<br />
        Launch Status: Scheduled November 28, 2025
      </p>
    </section>

